a Edwards]], English journalist and author (d. 1892) *[[1837]] &ndash; [[Alois Hitler]], Austrian civil servant (d. 1903) *[[1840]] &ndash; [[Carlota of Mexico]] (d. 1927) *[[1845]] &ndash; [[Leopold Auer]], Hungarian violinist, composer, and conductor (d. 1930) *[[1847]] &ndash; [[George Washington Ball]], American legislator from Iowa (d. 1915) *[[1848]] &ndash; [[Paul Gauguin]], French painter and sculptor (d. 1903) *[[1851]] &ndash; [[Ture Malmgren]], Swedish journalist and politician (d. 1922) *[[1862]] &ndash; [[Philipp Lenard]], Slovak-German physicist and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Physics|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 1947) *[[1863]] &ndash; [[Bones Ely]], American baseball player and manager (d. 1952) *[[1868]] &ndash; [[Charles Rennie Mackintosh]], Scottish painter and architect (d. 1928) *[[1877]] &ndash; [[Roelof Klein]], Dutch-American rower and engineer (d. 1960) *[[1879]] &ndash; [[Knud Rasmussen]], Danish anthropologist and explorer (d. 1933) * 1879 &ndash; [[Joan Voûte]], Dutch astronomer and academic (d. 1963) *[[1884]] &ndash; [[Ester Claesson]], Swedish landscape architect (d. 1931) *[[1883]] &ndash; [[Sylvanus Morley]], American archaeologist and scholar (d. 1948) *[[1886]] &ndash; [[Henri Coandă]], Romanian engineer, designed the [[Coandă-1910]] (d. 1972) *[[1888]] &ndash; [[Clarence DeMar]], American runner and educator (d. 1958) *[[1892]] &ndash; [[Leo Reise]], Canadian ice hockey player (d. 1975) *[[1893]] &ndash; [[Gillis Grafström]], Swedish figure skater and architect (d. 1938) *[[1894]] &ndash; [[Alexander P. de Seversky]], Georgian-American pilot and engineer, co-designed the [[Republic P-47 Thunderbolt]] (d. 1974) *[[1896]] &ndash; [[Douglas Campbell (aviator)|Douglas Campbell]], American lieutenant and pilot (d. 1990) * 1896 &ndash; [[Robert S. Mulliken]], American physicist and chemist, [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 1986) * 1896 &ndash; [[Imre Nagy]], Hungarian soldier and politician, 44th [[List of Prime Minist