{{unsourced|date=July 2015}} {{Infobox music festival | | music_festival_name = Puntala-Rock | image = | image_size = | caption = | location = [[Lempäälä]], [[Finland]] | years_active = 1982-1991, 2000–present | dates = Two days, last Weekend in July with a 1-day warm-up in [[Tampere]] | genre = [[Punk rock music|Punk]], [[punk rock]], [[Crust punk]], [[HC punk]], [[Thrash metal]], [[Post-punk]] | website = {{URL|www.puntala-rock.net/Puntala-Rock}} }}
'''Puntala-Rock''' is a [[punk rock]] [[festival]] in [[Lempäälä]], [[Finland]] and is one of the oldest and largest [[punk rock festivals]] in Finland. It is an important punk-cultural happening in a Finish point of view, because similar punk-rock festivals are not held in Finland. The main organizer is the [[Lempäälän karuselli | Lempäälän karuselli ry (LeKa)]].
Puntala-Rock history begins in 1980. In 1990s it was quiet, but in 2000, the event returned. The festival will take place in the last weekend of July. The festival are held on Puntala camp area, located approximately 15 km from the center of Lempäälä to wards [[Pirkkala]].
Puntala-Rock has no age-limit.
